{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:32:27.206549+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I understand the situation. The issue asks to update the report pipeline to label ports as \"allowed\" or \"unexpected\" based on the local policy file (`policy/allowed_ports.yml`).\n\nCurrently, `scripts/classify_ports.py` has a hardcoded set of allowed ports `{8080}`, but it should read from `policy/allowed_ports.yml` instead. I'll update the script to properly use the policy file.\n\nLet me implement the changes:", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 695, "prompt_tokens": 10599, "total_tokens": 11294, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 193, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 10368, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0007424598, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001378098, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00060465}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780965126-JII8HGVs58tyhVpVzLKe", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9cb-320b-7be3-afc3-2b1f53d68adc-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "create_or_update_file", "args": {"branch": "main", "content": "#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport json\nimport yaml\n\nnormalized = Path('reports/normalized_scan.json')\nif not normalized.exists():\n    raise SystemExit('Run scripts/normalize_nmap_xml.py first')\n\npolicy_path = Path('policy/allowed_ports.yml')\nif not policy_path.exists():\n    raise SystemExit('Policy file not found: policy/allowed_ports.yml')\n\npolicy = yaml.safe_load(policy_path.read_text())\nallowed_ports = set()\nfor entry in policy.ge