{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:33:04.332557+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I don't have write access to the repository with the current token (both commit methods return 403). Let me report what I found and the complete solution I've prepared.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Issue #3: \"Add allowed-port classification\"\n\n### Problem\nThe report pipeline needs to label ports as \"allowed\" or \"unexpected\" based on the local policy file (`policy/allowed_ports.yml`), rather than using a hardcoded set of ports.\n\n### Current State\n- **`policy/allowed_ports.yml`** — Contains a YAML list of allowed ports (currently just port 8080 for TCP).\n- **`scripts/classify_ports.py`** — Has a **hardcoded** `allowed = {8080}` set instead of reading from the policy file.\n- **`reports/port_classification.md`** — A placeholder report with no actual table data.\n\n### Proposed Changes\n\n**1. `scripts/classify_ports.py`** — Update to read from `policy/allowed_ports.yml` using PyYAML:\n\n```python\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport json\nimport yaml\n\nnormalized = Path('reports/normalized_scan.json')\nif not normalized.exists():\n    raise SystemExit('Run scripts/normalize_nmap_xml.py first')\n\npolicy_path = Path('policy/allowed_ports.yml')\nif not policy_path.exists():\n    raise SystemExit('Policy file not found: policy/allowed_ports.yml')\n\npolicy = yaml.safe_load(policy_path.read_text())\nallowed_ports = set()\nfor entry in policy.get('allowed_ports', []):\n    allowed_ports.add(entry['port'])\n\ndata = json.loads(normalized.read_text())\nrows = []\nfor item in data['ports']:\n    label = 'allowed' if item['port'] in allowed_ports else 'unexpected'\n    rows.append(f\"| {item['protocol']} | {item['port']} | {item['service']} | {label} |\")\n\nout = Path('reports/port_classification.md')\nout.parent.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\nout.write_text(\n    '# Port Classification\\n\\n'\n    '| Protocol | Port | Service | Label |\\n'\n    '| --- | --- | --- | --- |\\n'\n    + '\\n'.join(rows) + '\\n'\n)\nprint(out)\n```\n\n**2. `policy/allowed_ports.yml`** — Already contains the correct policy data; no changes needed.\n\n**3. `reports/port_classification.md`** — Will be auto-generated by running the updated script.\n\n### Limitation\n⚠️ **I was unable to commit these changes** because the GitHub token only has read access (both `create_or_update_file` and `push_files` returned HTTP 403). The changes above are ready to be applied by someone with write access.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 606, "prompt_tokens": 11681, "total_tokens": 12287, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 37, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 11136, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0008043846, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002771646, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00052722}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780965163-FxXmNZlylhgSpcy5AupA", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9cb-c1ac-71c2-aa88-94635f004abd-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 11681, "output_tokens": 606, "total_tokens": 12287, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 11136}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 37}}}}]}}}
